2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses interference alignment in the context of the K-user interference channel, which is a common problem in wireless networking. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper may be relevant to the study of interference in social networks or other types of information networks. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may be relevant to the study of interference in multimedia communication systems. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper may be relevant to the study of interference in computational systems, such as those used in finance or scientific simulations.
